properties.popupContent: Beetle: Wonder if it was a species Darwin hunted?
Wading: Good job I wore welly's!
Boggy Patch: Too wet even for welly's!
Bee: Heavily laden with pollen, either tired or got a bit squished, moved to the shade on a stick.
A butterfly, a common blue(?), dances to and fro, its electric hue around us meanders.
Fallen Hawthorn. Very windy today, but not THAT windy!
Investigate ladder at bank pushed into river - must be to help swimmers get in and out.
Keep having to dodge the cyclists so headed back toward river.
Try path over here, but very boggy and gave up and headed back to river.
Getting weary of the strong wind, so cut the corner off.
Time for a drink in the pub of course!
Blossom tree in the beer garden looks splendid, like a perfect cloud resting on a stick.

properties.name: Smell the blossom, smell the cow dung. Both come in waves.
